# FortiGate VLAN Interface Plan

This plan is rendered from `ansible/group_vars/fortigates.yml`.

## Assumptions

- FortiGate is the gateway/firewall for all VLANs.
- FortiGate uses `.2` as the gateway convention.
- VDOM: `{{ fortigate_vdom }}`
- Parent interface: `{{ fortigate_parent_interface }}`
- Apply is blocked until `fortigate_parent_interface` is replaced and `CONFIRM_FORTIGATE_APPLY=yes` is set.

## Candidate Interfaces

| Interface | VLAN | IP | Access | Alias | Role |
|---|---:|---|---|---|---|
{% for item in fortigate_vlan_interfaces -%}
| {{ item.name }} | {{ item.vlanid }} | {{ item.ip }} | {{ item.allowaccess | join(',') }} | {{ item.alias }} | {{ item.role }} |
{% endfor %}

## Validation Commands

```text
show system interface
get system interface
execute ping-options source 10.10.10.2
execute ping 10.10.10.1
```

## Rollback Hint

Remove only the VLAN interfaces created by this plan after confirming no firewall policies or DHCP services depend on them.
